14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1056.topic&index=141>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fixing the warriors in PoP and addressing taunt concerns</span><hr size=1> The two types of AC (avoidance and mitigation) function very differently. <br>
<br>
Avoidance AC is checked against a random roll and a portion of the attacker's atk to see whether you get hit or missed. Avoidance AC is made up from defense skill and AGI, with monks getting an extra ~230? avoidance AC just for being a monk and not going over the weight limit. Gear has no effect on avoidance beyond increasing AGI. The avoidance portion of AC cannot be raised except by increasing defense skill (which is capped) and adding AGI (which is capped).<br>
<br>
Mitigation AC is what is checked after the combat engine has determined that you have been hit. Your mitigation is compared to a random roll and a portion of the attacker's atk rating to determine how much damage you will take. You cannot take less than a certain amount of damage regardless of how much mitigation AC you have. Mitigation AC is made up mainly of the raw AC from gear, along with a lesser contribution from the defense skill.<br>
<br>
Pre ROK, monks had much higher defense and better secondary avoidance skills like block. They also had much, much lower raw AC from items. Monks got hit less often than warriors did, but took more damage when they did get hit. Warriors at the time had about 50% more hp than monks did, which in the long run made them the better tanks for anything that was moderately difficult.<br>
<br>
Now, the situation is different. It isn't terribly difficult for a monk to get the same <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> effective</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mitigation AC as a warrior (due to the effects of mitigation AC being tiny after a certain point) and still have much better avoidance. A monk with 1300 AC will have less mitigation AC than a warrior with 1300 AC, but more avoidance. A monk with 1400+ AC will have essentially the same mitigation AC, but much better avoidance. Mitigation AC is broken, that is the problem.<br>
<br>
<br>
At the same time, the hp difference between warriors and monks has shrunk drastically due to all/all gear to the point where it isn't out of the ordinary for high end warriors to only have about a 20% hp advantage over monks, when it used to be 50%. Now do you see the problem? <br>
<br>
Monks effectively tank much better relative to warriors than they ever did before, have nifty utility abilities like FD, sneak, mend, and ID, and do considerably more damage than warriors do. This is all supposed to be balanced by the weight penalty. With the amount of 0.0 weight, ALL/ALL items with high AC and high hp, that penalty is gone.  <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>
