</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umetzenmegablades.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Metzen Megablades</A> at: 9/2/02 7:41:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhyardgune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/2/02 9:57:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1056.topic&index=158>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uh...</span><hr size=1> I'm gonna skip the last 2 pages of Monk discussion because I just don't care and go back to an earlier part of the thread.  <br>
<br>
In a Seb xp grind group heading for the discoes, you have everything except a tank and you suddenly see /ooc Warlord lfg and /ooc 56 Pally lfg, hmmm, who to take???  I'd take the Pally.  Sure, 4 levels lower, but guess what, no problems with aggro.  The Warlord will do what every Warrior has ever done, mash the Taunt button, wait 6 seconds, mash the Taunt button, pray your weapon procs while waiting the next 6 seconds to mash the Taunt button and peel the mob off the Rogue.  The 56 Pally casts Flash of Light (level 9 spell) and instantly has aggro.  If the Pally loses aggro, well that's nothing a stun or another Flash of Light can't fix within a couple seconds.  Plus the 56 Pally can backup heal, buff, root, stun.  The Warlord on the hand can...ummmmm...<br>
<br>
As for damage mitigation in this case, there is no difference, the Pally likely has enough AC where it won't matter and chances are you're not using Defensive on Frogloks.  So the Cleric has to CH a bit more, but then again the cleric never has to heal the Rogue because the stupid Taunt button isn't doing anything.<br>
<br>
There is absolutely no purpose to having a Warrior in an xp grind group if there is a Knight available, there just isn't.  We can't acquire or hold aggro with anywhere close to a Knight's consistency.  Our dps is FAR lower than Monks, Rogues, or Rangers with a clear bow shot and is only slightly better than a 2H equipped Knight.  We can't snare, buff, or add anything usable to the group.<br>
<br>
I am absolutely opposed to mobs getting damage bonuses when attacking other classes, that's just plain stupid.  Most high end mobs already hit hard enough, there is no reason for the chanters to die even faster.<br>
<br>
I also think that the Knights should be as good as Warriors in terms of tanking ability, that all 3 classes should have an equal value in a group.  Since succesful tanking requires the ability to acquire and maintain aggro and the Knights have spells uniquely suited to that purpose, there needs to be some balancing done in other areas.  AC is a wash, forget about changing that, it won't happen, plus any changes would further widen the gap between the uber-guild/uber-twink Haves and the Have-Nots who don't have those advantages.<br>
<br>
Some sort of skill or innate ability that reduces damage taken would go a long way towards helping repair the gross imbalance that currently exists.  VI can scrap the Defensive disc if that's the price we have to pay for innate Warrior-only damage reduction.  How about a Block skill tied directly to our Dual Wield ability so we have a chance to Block with an offhand weapon?<br>
<br>
The Taunt skill needs to be improved or changed, period.  The more I think about it and the lame &quot;but if we improve Taunt then the game will be trivialized&quot; arguement, the more I realize just how much BS it is.  The only thing trivialized is Warriors.  Knights can grab and hold aggro without even touching the Taunt button.  Instant, nearly permanent aggro.  If that doesn't trivialize most encounters, I don't know what will.  Warriors on the other hand get to mash the Taunt button every 6 seconds and pray that our weapons proc.<br>
<br>
Other needed improvements for Warriors besides some kind of innate damage reduction and a workable Taunt skill...<br>
<br>
Lesser versions of Enraging Blow weapons since 99% of all Warriors will NEVER see these weapons except in someone else's hands.  Something to bridge the gap between the Willsappers/Wavecrashers/Frostys and the EB weapons that drop off mobs that only uber guilds ever see.<br>
<br>
Make Severilious spawnable only and on less than a one week timer.  Or do something like the Druid version of Fay where only the quest spawned version drops the Green Scale.  The Epic is hard enough without having to pay 75k to the manaburn team that shredded the poor lizard 15 minutes after the patch was done.<br>
<br>
Increase Piercing so that it caps at the same level as every other weapon skill.  It's a very minor point, but really, is a spear THAT much harder to use than mace or sword?<br>
<br>
Give Warriors and Warriors alone an increased damage bonus to boost our dps some.  The sacred 1.0:1.2:1.4 ratio is bs, it's closer to 1.0:1.5:2.0.  Instead of the (level-25)/3 formula, maybe something like (level-24)/2 for the mainhand weapon and (level-24)/6 for the offhand weapon.  At 60, that would be 18/6 rather than the current 11/0, not a huge increase but something to make us more effective at combat...that is what we are supposed to be good at, right? <p>Hyardgune Varangian <BR> 57 Ogre Myrmidon of Gathered Might</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhyardgune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyardgune</A> at: 9/2/02 10:01:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukedintheoneeyed.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kedin the one eyed </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/2/02 10:58:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1056.topic&index=159>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uh...</span><hr size=1> hehe all i can say is my eyes were bugging after all that reading, plus i had been up for nearly 24 hours (12 hour shifts and start of my weekend lol) <p>> > <h6 align="center"><img src="http://blissett.net/eq/sigs/sig_kedin.jpg"
